<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 02 at 7:11PM CDT  by NWS Wichita</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Montgomery and eastern Chautauqua Counties through 745 PM CDT...
At 711 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bigheart, or 14 miles south of Sedan, moving northeast at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Caney, Sedan, Tyro, Peru, Chautauqua, Havana, Elgin, Niotaze and
Hale.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for southeastern
Kansas.</instruction>
